  "body": "If you have a component that sets context and a child gets passed in through props that supports that context, it will not render when the context updates - only a render from the component that passes in the child will call render and update the child.\n\nExample:\nhttp://jsbin.com/ficoyutusa/1/edit?js,output\n\nAnother example:\nThis one works (Parent has its own context): http://jsbin.com/cinebaripu/1/edit?html,js,console,output\nThis one does not (Parent removes its context): http://jsbin.com/niyetupida/1/edit?html,js,console,output\n",
